<div id="review_3499278857" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3499278857" />
    <a title="Gilda Felt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16463173-gilda-felt"><img alt="Gilda Felt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1474832489p2/16463173.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3499278857?book_show_action=true">Aug 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gilda Felt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gilda Felt" href="/user/show/16463173-gilda-felt">Gilda Felt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3499278857" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14726600578720958556">Once again, Shaara brings to life the men who fought in the Civil War, on both sides. Even though that obviously fictional you can’t help but feel for what they’re going through. And while Grant’s reputation is enhanced, while that of Bragg’s is denigrated. This is the man the South insists on naming a fort after? Not only is he a traitor, but he appears to have been not a very good general.<br/><br/>I’m looking forward to the fourth, and last book dealing with the Western Theatre. I’ll miss Grant, who wa</span>
  <span id="freeText14726600578720958556" style="display:none">Once again, Shaara brings to life the men who fought in the Civil War, on both sides. Even though that obviously fictional you can’t help but feel for what they’re going through. And while Grant’s reputation is enhanced, while that of Bragg’s is denigrated. This is the man the South insists on naming a fort after? Not only is he a traitor, but he appears to have been not a very good general.<br /><br />I’m looking forward to the fourth, and last book dealing with the Western Theatre. I’ll miss Grant, who was elevated to command the entire Northern army, but I’m looking forward to reading how Sherman does. We know the outcome, but Shaara has a way of getting into the minds of these men. We’ve seen how well Sherman does when in a secondary position; it will be interesting to read about him in the lead role.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14726600578720958556" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


