<span id="freeTextContainer4513628529082513688">I have read all of Shaara&apos;s books and have never found fault with any of them. This latest work is another faultless addition to this author&apos;s body of work. While all of his books are classified historical fiction this is only because all the dialogue contained in the books is invented. Shaara, however, invents his dialogues with meticulous care and accuracy to the character being featured that it only enhances the history. While I know he is working on a Korean War book and his present series h</span>
  <span id="freeText4513628529082513688" style="display:none">I have read all of Shaara's books and have never found fault with any of them. This latest work is another faultless addition to this author's body of work. While all of his books are classified historical fiction this is only because all the dialogue contained in the books is invented. Shaara, however, invents his dialogues with meticulous care and accuracy to the character being featured that it only enhances the history. While I know he is working on a Korean War book and his present series has another addition yet to come I do wish he could consider a book not involving war. I would think there are American historical events worthy of Shaara's attention and would love to read his treatment of them.</span>
